    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The experience you're having really does sound distressing, but it's still very unlikely that someone could be programming your dreams, especially with such specific memories. Dreams often incorporate small details from our environment or daily lives—a phenomenon known as a 'false memory' where fragments of stimuli are misremembered as being dreamt episodes. The specific brand \"Vigorade\" could just be a part of your everyday life that your subconscious is paying attention to. To ease your concerns, maintaining good sleep hygiene can be beneficial. Avoid intense or vivid content before bed, stay positively oriented, and if you're worried, a mental health professional could help you understand these experiences better.",
      "source": "target",
